  "cascade_cli_help": "usage: cascade [-h] [--version]\n               {stats,chains,init,watch,list,inspect,pin,export,observe,fingerprint,entities,pii,provenance,ingest,analyze,proxy,hold,hold-status} ...\n\nCASCADE - Universal AI Provenance Layer\n\npositional arguments:\n  {stats,chains,init,watch,list,inspect,pin,export,observe,fingerprint,entities,pii,provenance,ingest,analyze,proxy,hold,hold-status}\n                        Commands\n    stats               Show lattice statistics\n    chains              List all chains\n    init                Show setup instructions\n    watch               Watch live observations\n    list                List recent observations\n    inspect             Inspect an observation\n    pin                 Pin observation to IPFS\n    export              Export lattice/chain to JSON\n    observe             Manual observation\n    fingerprint         Fingerprint a model\n    entities            Entity resolution\n    pii                 Scan for PII\n    provenance          Data provenance\n    ingest              Ingest logs/files\n    analyze             Analyze logs/files\n    proxy               Start proxy server\n    hold                Show HOLD usage and API info\n    hold-status         Show HOLD system status\n\noptions:\n  -h, --help            show this help message and exit\n  --version, -v         Show version\n\nExamples:\n  cascade stats                    Show lattice statistics\n  cascade list -n 20               List recent observations\n  cascade chains                   List all chains\n  cascade inspect <root>           Inspect an observation\n  cascade watch                    Live observation feed\n  cascade proxy                    Start proxy server\n  cascade fingerprint <model>      Fingerprint a model\n  cascade pii <file>               Scan file for PII\n  cascade ingest <path>            Ingest logs/files"
}